@name         Enhanced style for Sortd Smart Skin for Gmail
@description  The letter spacing in task descriptions was made slightly wider. The column headers were changed from uppercase to lowercase. By default, tasks are fully colored, which creates a Christmas tree effect when using many colors. Instead they now have a colored left bar. By default, when highlighted, only the description text gets a colored background. This was changed into a fully colored background with a subtle diagonal stripe. The color picker was improved by adding a black border on mouse hover. The follow-up icon (flag) was changed from grey to red. In the Today view (Ctrl-Space) the background colors were changed from white into lightyellow (Today) and lightblue (Earlier).
@namespace    ocor61.blogspot
@version      1.0.0
@author       OmeCor <ocor61@gmail.com> (ocor61.blogspot.com)
@homepageURL  https://ocor61.blogspot.com/2019/05/user-style-sortd.html
@license      unlicense
@preprocessor stylus
==/UserStyle== */

